Let me analyze this task systematically:

Main Target Image Analysis:
- Structure consists of 3 blocks
- Colors: Blue cube, Yellow rectangular block, Two orange cylindrical blocks
- Layers: 2 layers (orange cylinders at bottom, yellow block in middle, blue cube on top)
- Spatial Arrangement: Orange cylinders form base, yellow block placed horizontally on cylinders, blue cube placed on yellow block

Block Dictionary Identification:
- Blue Cube: Block Index 1
- Yellow Rectangular Block (Horizontal): Block Index 6
- Orange Cylinders: Block Index 13

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 13 (first orange cylinder)
    Step2: Move block with index 13 (second orange cylinder)
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (yellow rectangular block)
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
}

This sequence exactly matches the structure in the main target image, using blocks from the dictionary without any rotation.
